GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_MoatLeverage> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_MoatLeverage> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#MoatLeverage> ;
    narr:childCount "19"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "0aa9e9af614ab672ef57f5b0c062b90c95e5487f" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks aswritten's evolving account of its own defensibility across technical, architectural, and political registers. The earliest and most durable layer is the [extraction pipeline as moat](narr:Narrative_MoatExtractionProcess), articulated in March 2026: the consumer receives compiled perspective, not source documents, and cannot reconstruct the original content — a position reinforced by [Scarlet's direct quote](narr:Obs_ScarletMoatQuote) naming perspective-extraction and citability as the real differentiator. This technical core was extended in June 2026 by the [processor-not-store framing](narr:Narrative_ProcessorNotStore), which repositions the moat away from data custody entirely toward the transformation process, enabling zero-retention compliance — a framing that [an enterprise consultant immediately played back](narr:Obs_DiscoveryConsultantPlayback) with the two-pipe model added. The [graph-plus-LLM combination](narr:Narrative_GraphLLMMoat) adds a second technical layer: emergent behavior from facts and value statements traversed together, claimed as non-replicable by either component alone. Architecturally, the [git-native worldview](narr:Position_Differentiation_1) distinguishes aswritten from runtime-layer competitors, while [upstream knowledge extraction](narr:Position_Differentiation_2) addresses a gap agent platforms leave open. The [publish-liberally decision](narr:Position_PublishLiberallyDecision) sharpens what the moat actually is: the transformation pipeline and accumulated graph, not the ideas. By June 2025, the [Fable 5 takedown](narr:Narrative_FableWakeUpCall) radicalized the anti-lock-in argument into a political claim — ownership of expertise-enabling context as means of production — sitting above, not replacing, the pain-led pitch. The [GitHub analogy](narr:Narrative_GitHubAnalogy) frames the whole as infrastructure-category creation. A newer thread, [AI-to-AI provenance](narr:Narrative_AItoAIProvenance), introduces a pattern where AI-generated content enters collective memory with human as curator, not author, claimed as a novel moat dimension. The [irreducible lens](narr:Obs_DesignCollaboratorLensIrreducibleQuote) (July 2026) and the [trust contract](narr:Narrative_TrustContractWedge) as delegatable-agent wedge extend the defensibility argument into organizational and relational territory.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AItoAIProvenance> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_FableWakeUpCall> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_GitHubAnalogy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_GraphLLMMoat> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MoatExtractionProcess> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ProcessorNotStore> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_TrustContractWedge> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DesignCollaboratorLensIrreducibleQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DiscoveryConsultantPlayback> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_FableAntiLockInPolitics> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_MoatLeverage> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NatureOfExpertiseQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ProcessorNotStore> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletMoatQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_Differentiation_1> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_Differentiation_2> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_MoatCreatorOwnsData> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PublishLiberallyDecision> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_ProprietaryMoat> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The real differentiator and the technical moat is that I take textual documents and I extract perspective from them and then I make that perspective citable in the individual task." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletMoatQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Creator owns data, not consumer. Consumer receives compiled perspective, not source documents. Even with the raw repo, the extraction process (source → transactions → compilable graph) is the real defensibility." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_MoatCreatorOwnsData> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The entire knowledge graph is stored as SPARQL in the customer repo. aswritten's role is processor, never store." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ProcessorNotStore> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The moat is the transformation pipeline and the accumulated graph, not the ideas." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PublishLiberallyDecision> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "No company would develop software without GitHub. No company should deploy AI agents without versioned organizational context." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_GitHubAnalogy> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "proprietary (it reveals the compiled knowledge graph — a moat)" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_ProprietaryMoat> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Proprietary system, 7 org case studies, deep deployment knowledge cited as durable moat even in failure scenario." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_MoatLeverage> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The combination of facts + value statements in a graph, traversed by an LLM, produces emergent behavior neither can achieve alone." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_GraphLLMMoat> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The political/means-of-production framing (Fable 5, June 2026) sits explicitly 'above, not in place of' the pain-led pitch — raising the question of whether the manifesto register helps or overreaches the product argument." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_FableWakeUpCall> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_FableAntiLockInPolitics> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Human irreplaceability claim — expertise as selection of what to do and when — runs in tension with the AI-to-AI provenance thread, where human is curator not author." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NatureOfExpertiseQuote> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AItoAIProvenance> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Processor-not-store repositions the moat away from data custody, but the earlier creator-owns-data framing emphasizes custody-adjacent non-reconstructibility — the two framings are compatible but not identical in what they defend." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ProcessorNotStore> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MoatExtractionProcess> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_MoatCreatorOwnsData> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Publish-liberally decision (June 2026) explicitly concedes the ideas are not the moat — an outlier against any reading that treats the graph's conceptual novelty as defensibility." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_PublishLiberallyDecision> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "AI-to-AI provenance as moat is introduced without a dated validation signal, leaving it as an asserted pattern rather than a confirmed differentiator." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AItoAIProvenance> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}